29/05/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) President Dragan Cavic issued a stern warning on Wednesday (28 May) in advance of the Pope's visit to the entity.
He said police would ensure maximum security for the Pontiff and up to 150,000 pilgrims, expected to attend mass in the RS capital on 22 June.
About 3,500 officers will be on patrol during the visit.
SFOR is expected to call in extra troops for the event.
In other news, SFOR reported that its soldiers have found more than three tonnes of bombs hidden in a car dump in Mostar.
A spokesman for the peacekeepers said the area has been sealed off until bomb disposal teams finish removing the explosives.
(AFP - 28/05/03)
